<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.207860>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 9. Mukaria lii. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (2) Head and thorax, lateral view; (3) Forewing; (4) Hindwing; (5) male pygofer, dorsal view; (6) Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (7) aedeagus, connective and styles, dorsal view; (8) aedeagus, caudal view; (9) female sternite VII. Scale bars: = 2 mm (Figs 1, 2, 8); 1 mm (Figs 3, 4); 0.5 mm (Figs 5 – 7, 9)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/207860/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.207863>
    dc:description "FIGURE 24. Distribution of Mukaria species. M. albinotata (); M. bambusana (); M. confersa (); M. flavida (); M. lii sp. nov. (); M. maculata (); M. nigra (); M. pallipes (); M. penthimioides (); M. splendida (); M. testacea (); M. variabilis (); M. zonata ()." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/207863/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

